se. Good  Private schools are an incentive for poor public schools to get better, because if they don't, they will lose more and more students.   This is a free country and people should have the freedom to send their kids to whatever school they choose and one that supports the moral philosophy that the parents are trying to instill at home.  I think tax money allocated to schools should be divided equally among all the school age children in the district. The money allocated for each child should be given to the parent(s) to send the child to any school they wish. This would give a strong incentive for all schools to offer the best education possible for the taxpayers dollar, and the competition would also lower the overall cost of education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1062" language="en" documentId="3190" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Daniel902" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:36PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="3190" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1062"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>